title: Woodsboro and Frederick Turnpike Company Tollhouse
text:
The Woodsboro and Frederick Turnpike Company Tollhouse is a historic <a href="toll%20house">toll house</a> located at <a href="Walkersville%2C%20Maryland">Walkersville</a>, <a href="Frederick%20County%2C%20Maryland">Frederick County</a>, <a href="Maryland">Maryland</a>, <a href="United%20States">United States</a>. It is a two-story brick structure over a stone foundation, with a small interior end chimney at each <a href="gable">gable</a> end. It was used as a tollhouse by the <a href="Woodsboro%20and%20Frederick%20Turnpike%20Company">Woodsboro and Frederick Turnpike Company</a>.
The Woodsboro and Frederick Turnpike Company Tollhouse was listed on the <a href="National%20Register%20of%20Historic%20Places">National Register of Historic Places</a> in 1979.
